You are a study assistant.
Turn the following notes into flashcards.

Return valid JSON only in this format:
{
  "cards": [
    { "front": "question", "back": "answer" }
  ]
}

Create 8 to 12 useful flashcards.
Do not include any text outside the JSON.

Notes:
Cells are the basic unit of life. Mitochondria produce ATP.

```json
{
  "cards": [
    {
      "front": "What is the fundamental structural and functional unit of all known living organisms?",
      "back": "Cells"
    },
    {
      "front": "The cell is considered the basic unit of what?",
      "back": "Life"
    },
    {
      "front": "Which cellular organelle is primarily responsible for generating most of the cell's supply of adenosine triphosphate (ATP)?",
      "back": "Mitochondria"
    },
    {
      "front": "What is the main energy currency molecule produced by mitochondria?",
      "back": "ATP (Adenosine Triphosphate)"
    },
    {
      "front": "What term describes the essential building blocks that make up all living things?",
      "back": "Cells"
    },
    {
      "front": "The process of cellular respiration, which produces ATP, mainly takes place in which part of the cell?",
      "back": "Mitochondria"
    },
    {
      "front": "If 'cells' are the basic unit of life, what are 'mitochondria' known for producing?",
      "back": "ATP"
    },
    {
      "front": "What is the name of the energy-carrying molecule vital for cellular functions?",
      "back": "ATP"
    }
  ]
}
```

