```json
{
  "questions": [
    {
      "question_text": "What is considered the basic unit of all known living organisms?",
      "question_type": "multiple_choice",
      "choices": [
        "A. Tissues",
        "B. Cells",
        "C. Organs",
        "D. Molecules"
      ],
      "answer": {
        "correct": "B"
      },
      "explanation": "Cells are the fundamental structural and functional units of all living things."
    },
    {
      "question_text": "Which cellular organelle is responsible for producing ATP?",
      "question_type": "multiple_choice",
      "choices": [
        "A. Nucleus",
        "B. Ribosome",
        "C. Mitochondrion",
        "D. Golgi apparatus"
      ],
      "answer": {
        "correct": "C"
      },
      "explanation": "Mitochondria are often referred to as the 'powerhouses' of the cell because they generate most of the cell's supply of adenosine triphosphate (ATP)."
    },
    {
      "question_text": "What is the primary role of mitochondria in cellular biology?",
      "question_type": "multiple_choice",
      "choices": [
        "A. Storing genetic information",
        "B. Producing ATP",
        "C. Synthesizing proteins",
        "D. Transporting waste products"
      ],
      "answer": {
        "correct": "B"
      },
      "explanation": "Mitochondria are specialized organelles whose main function is to produce ATP, the energy currency of the cell."
    },
    {
      "question_text": "The statement 'Cells are the basic unit of life' implies that cells are the:",
      "question_type": "multiple_choice",
      "choices": [
        "A. Primary means of reproduction",
        "B. Main site for waste removal",
        "C. Smallest independently functioning living entity",
        "D. Repository for all cellular DNA"
      ],
      "answer": {
        "correct": "C"
      },
      "explanation": "Cells are the smallest entities that can be considered living, performing all essential life functions."
    },
    {
      "question_text": "What substance is produced by mitochondria and serves as the main energy source for cellular activities?",
      "question_type": "multiple_choice",
      "choices": [
        "A. Glucose",
        "B. DNA",
        "C. ATP",
        "D. RNA"
      ],
      "answer": {
        "correct": "C"
      },
      "explanation": "ATP (Adenosine Triphosphate) is the molecule that stores and releases energy for use in cellular processes, and it is primarily produced by mitochondria."
    }
  ]
}
```

